summary: Just listened to the GoT podcast “Still Watching” with Joanna Robinson and Richard Lawson and they interviewed Paula Fairfield...
body:
Just listened to the GoT podcast “Still Watching” with Joanna Robinson and Richard Lawson and they interviewed Paula Fairfield who is the sound designer. Fairfield mentioned that there will be some other almost extinct creatures in the next two episodes, which makes me think we may get some direwolf sounds…. maybe Nymeria???

Some possible thoughts about Nymeria returning

•Arya and The Hound run into her on the kings road and Arya has a realization that Nymeria isn’t actually alone with her pack

•Nymeria joins them or somehow shows up in KL (with how the writing has been totes possible) and helps to save to Arya from the mountain or some imminent death and dies herself, leading Arya to realize she never really is alone nor should be alone along with a speech from Sandor

These are my dreams and hopes rn. Also I enjoy weekly podcast and recommend

summary: The more I think about it...
title: The more I think about it...
body:
Even though it made me sad that Arya rejected Gendry, I really like the way it was done. She couldn’t offer him something that she is not, and she wasn’t going to change for a man. However, she didn’t ask him to give up anything for her either. If they don’t end up together in the end, it’s not a case of not loving or caring about each other, but a case of wanting different things in life. 

The look on her face and the way she kissed him; I don’t think I’ve ever seen Arya be that tender and soft before. I really do believe that Arya loves him, and loving someone sometimes means letting them go and wanting them to be happy, even if it’s not with them. 

Excuse me while I continue to cry in a corner…

I still have hope.

summary: And will you continue to ship them, no matter what happens in the next episodes?
question: And will you continue to ship them, no matter what happens in the next episodes?
answer: Yes! Maybe because it never seemed possible and was always destined to end dramatically and serve a lot of Angst I am now shipping them even more than when they were happy. Gives so much space for FF! And I do think that we will get more epic Jonerys in the next episodes, otherwise why even bother make them fall in love? If Jon wanted to use her and betray her as soon as ge got the chance etc. that would have been pointless. But I still hope to see more of Jons feelings towards her in the next episodes.
